Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.10,0:01:43.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,假设外星人真的存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Suppose extraterrestrials truly exist
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.10,0:01:46.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们将要访问地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and want to tour Planet Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.10,0:01:50.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像我们最期待的那种星际旅行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they'd be in for the ultimate cosmic vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.11,0:01:56.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的名称来源于希腊语\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth, whose name may go back to the Greek name"eraze" *,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.11,0:02:00.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,意为土地 是太阳系的第三颗行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}meaning"ground", is the third terrestrial planet from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.12,0:02:07.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但当外星人到来时 他们会意识到地球的昵称--蓝色星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But when arriving, visitors will realize that it got its nickname,"the blue planet",
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.12,0:02:10.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为地球表面四分之三都是水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because three quarters of it is covered with water.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.13,0:02:12.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些来访者将发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And vacationers will see
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.13,0:02:16.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球是太阳系中唯一的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that Earth is the only planet in our solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.13,0:02:20.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生存着人类和其他高等生物的星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where humans, or thence life, exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.14,0:02:25.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果他们能在地球大气中或水下呼吸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you can breathe our oxygen-rich atmosphere, or breathe under water,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.14,0:02:31.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们就可以自由探索地球而无需空间飞行器或宇航服\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth can be explored without a protective spacecraft and space suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.15,0:02:36.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是他们得调整他们的表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But tourists will need to adjust their watches.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.15,0:02:40.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球绕太阳一圈是365天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It takes 365 days for Earth to orbit around the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.16,0:02:44.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每天是24小时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and each day is 24 hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.16,0:02:49.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是地球绕地轴旋转一圈所需要的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is the amount of time it takes the planet to rotate around its axis once.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.17,0:02:55.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管他们可能遇到飓风和人类战争\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Despite travellers warnings about deadly storms and civil wars,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.17,0:03:04.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球仍是一个相对安全的目的地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth is a relatively safe adventure destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.18,0:03:11.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是个非常特别的星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth is a very special planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.19,0:03:12.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像一辆保时捷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just like a Porsche
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.19,0:03:14.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是一辆特别的跑车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a very special car.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.69,0:03:18.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,诞生在太阳系合适的位置上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our planet was formed in just the right place in the Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.20,0:03:21.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上太阳系中只有这个位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact it's the only place we know of in our entire Solar System
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.20,0:03:24.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,适合动植物的生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where plants and animals can live under natural conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.80,0:03:28.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,唐纳德·布朗李\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Renowned astronomer Donald Brownlee,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.70,0:03:31.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始进行他的宇宙赛车之旅\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has spent his career on a cosmic quest
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.68,0:03:34.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以解开原始地球之谜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to solve the mysteries surrounding the origin of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.96,0:03:40.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这场成为适合生命繁衍的星球的竞赛中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He says, in the race to become a life-sustaining planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.59,0:03:43.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,假设地球就是司机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth was in the driver's seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.82,0:03:47.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这场竞赛危机四伏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But he cautions the ride was full of danger and intrigue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.60,0:03:51.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球面临许多事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth had many things that happened to it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.13,0:03:54.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一切即将开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to make it the way it is right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.18,0:03:57.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些事件很多都伴随着幸运\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And many of these things did involve luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.57,0:04:05.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,45亿年前的宇宙某处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}4.5 billion years ago, one corner of the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.10,0:04:08.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经历了一场巨大的爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}experienced a colossal fireworks display.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.50,0:04:17.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常强大但短暂的大爆炸超新星爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A massive but short-lived star exploded as a supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.69,0:04:22.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸物在万有引力作用下坍塌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The blast from this star may have triggered the gravitational collapse
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.80,0:04:25.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中央形成了太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the cloud that formed the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.63,0:04:32.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很快地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Shortly after the Sun formed, you had
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.51,0:04:35.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,周围物质开始围绕太阳旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a lot of material orbiting around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.81,0:04:39.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些微小的冰粒 尘土\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this was microscopic stuff, ice particles, dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.10,0:04:44.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像干燥器上的棉绒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a lot of it wasn't unlike the lint that comes out of your dryer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.28,0:04:49.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,刚开始时集中成一小团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it began to kind of stick together in little clumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.54,0:04:53.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后其中一些变得像沙石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And eventually some of these pieces became more like sand,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.59,0:04:56.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大多是小块的硅酸盐石头 它们又不断地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}little pieces of silicate mostly, and it began to stick together
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.29,0:05:00.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,融合其他小石块\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you begin to get little rocks, little boulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.30,0:05:06.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不断的碰撞形成大石块\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the boulders grew larger, so did the collisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.30,0:05:10.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两个石块撞击后 引力使之结合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As two objects impacted, gravity held them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.31,0:05:18.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,保时捷跑车以极速闻名\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Porsches are known  for speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.31,0:05:22.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些小行星也如此\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Planets are also known for speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.32,0:05:25.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球形成时期 这些微粒 石块\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Earth was forming, particles and rocks and boulders
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.92,0:05:28.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通常以更快的速度 远快于保时捷跑车的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}came screaming in much faster than these cars
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.32,0:05:32.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像发生车祸一样碰撞在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}crash when they run into walls or other cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.73,0:05:40.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最初的地球形成于这些碰撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Through multiple collisions, infant Earth was formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.34,0:05:45.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要形成现在这么大的地球 还需要更多的碰撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it would take many more impacts for it to become the size it is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.35,0:05:52.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了更好的理解地球形成的过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To better understand the formation process,
