Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.12,0:06:58.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是普通枪子弹速度的10倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About 10 times the speed of a bullet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.09,0:07:05.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发射器将铝珠打入真空室\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's gonna be smashed to smithereens. The vertical gun will shoot the aluminium bead into the vacuum chamber
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.11,0:07:07.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,里面将充满地球早期大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}filled with atmospheric gases.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.44,0:07:10.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在用一堆沙子模拟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There it will impact a sandy mound
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.96,0:07:13.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,早期地球相似的地表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}resembling early Earth's surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.78,0:07:18.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的这个空间 除了稀薄大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're in a vacuum chamber but we'll be putting back in a gas
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.22,0:07:22.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,模拟一个可能的早期地球环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that will simulate what the early Earth must have looked like.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.33,0:07:26.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,弄一些坑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let's go ahead and make a bunch of craters,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.95,0:07:29.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大概像这样的早期地形\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what the early landscape of Earth must have looked like.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.99,0:07:34.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,碰撞一直存在 会有相当多的坑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cause these things would happen all the time, there had to have been a lot of craters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.89,0:07:40.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的碰撞计划 将击中这个表面的中央\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The plan is to come in, hit the centre of the target
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.48,0:07:44.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看看这些坑洼的表面会产生多大的破坏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and watch the crater form. And you'll see the destructive power
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.56,0:07:47.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然这是一个很小的物体\Nof… even tough it's a tiny bead,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.76,0:07:50.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也能产生足够的破坏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's gonna do some real serious damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.23,0:07:53.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没什么可以幸免\NCan you believe anything would survive…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.80,0:07:56.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高速摄像机记录着撞击过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}High-speed cameras will document the impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.85,0:08:00.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们从监视器上观察着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Schultz and Sugita, nervously watch the monitor
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.71,0:08:03.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在发射器之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}located outside the gun range.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.33,0:08:05.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个部分最激动人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the part that kills me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.02,0:08:09.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像暴风雨前夕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's like this moment before the storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.94,0:08:14.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,工程师在控制室操作着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From a secure control room, an engineer flips several switches.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.90,0:08:17.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的 就要开始了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ok. Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.84,0:08:22.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们开始祈祷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Schultz and Sugita mix science with a little superstition.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.57,0:08:24.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,交叉手指\NWe cross our fingers…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.78,0:08:26.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,腿\NCross our legs…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.35,0:08:29.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,手臂\NCross our hands…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.47,0:08:37.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太让人疯狂了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is what drives me nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.35,0:08:42.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,漂亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Oh, gorgeous! Oh, my gosh!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.64,0:08:46.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好了 让我们看看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ok, let's take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.60,0:08:49.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,试验情况如何\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The experiment worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.71,0:08:52.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,难以置信\NThat is unbelievably…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.78,0:08:54.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是否想起地球上的\NIf we imagine this on the Earth…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.73,0:08:55.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗯？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.82,0:08:58.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些云的变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These would be clouds that would be rolling
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.68,0:09:01.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跟龙卷风刮起的比较\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at velocities that'd be comparable to tornados.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.25,0:09:04.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更高 甚至更强大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}- Or even higher. - Even higher, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.10,0:09:08.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,录像显示出真实而恐怖的场景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The video taken reveals a frightening and realistic picture
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.48,0:09:10.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正是早期地球上所发生的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what happened on early Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.54,0:09:13.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,确实非常可怕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's a brilliant lake!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.93,0:09:16.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来看看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.27,0:09:25.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喔 天啊 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Oh, man! Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.00,0:09:31.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喔 实在是太梦幻了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That is absolutely gorgeous!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.76,0:09:33.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,造成如此大的破坏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That did some serious damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.46,0:09:39.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象一下地球上的这些小行星撞击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just imagine that this is the asteroid that slammed in to the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.67,0:09:42.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不断重复地发生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This must have been happening just repeatedly,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.39,0:09:44.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球表面造成严重的破坏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}doing real damage to the planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.05,0:09:46.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只是一个小实验\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's just a small scale example
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.80,0:09:49.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发生在早期地球的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what must have happened at the early Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.30,0:09:51.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真棒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.62,0:10:01.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些撞击地球的星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of the objects blasting into infant Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.38,0:10:04.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直径超过300英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were over 300 miles in diameter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.47,0:10:14.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种高强度撞击产生了超高温\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The force of one such high velocity impact created tremendous heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.99,0:10:18.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球内部开始变热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth began roasting from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.90,0:10:21.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,铁和镍融化 汇集到地核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Iron and nickel melted and sank to the core
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.96,0:10:24.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生巨大热量就像炼钢炉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}generating heat like a massive furnace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.25,0:10:29.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,岩石与融化液态的岩浆不停转换\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The outer rock, or magma, was completely melted
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.88,0:10:32.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,又产生大量的岩浆灰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}producing a molten ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.88,0:10:36.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球是飘浮在宇宙中的狂热地狱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The planet was a raging inferno floating in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.56,0:10:39.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完全的人间炼狱\Nliterally… hell on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.32,0:10:46.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,各种撞击更强烈地袭击地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The most severe impacts* could've sterilized the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.20,0:10:50.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球表面只有蒸汽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You've got a steam atmosphere and heat on the entire surface of the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.79,0:10:52.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且这样的高温 跟消毒柜一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}above sterilization temperatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.05,0:11:00.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地核的形成通常称之为铁核对流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Formation of the Earth's core, sometimes called the great iron catastrophe,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.16,0:11:04.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球诞生的最初4千万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}occurred within the first 40 million years of our planet's existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.02,0:11:08.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并对我们的未来产生了深远的影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it had a profound effect on our future.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.95,0:11:10.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,得益于地球的铁质核心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Within the iron core,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.62,0:11:15.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不断旋转对流逐渐产生了地磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the rotating ball of molten iron generated a remarkable magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.74,0:11:20.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是地球适合生存的必须条件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This set up the conditions for a habitable planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.20,0:11:24.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地心铁的聚集\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By getting all the iron down to the centre of the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.26,0:11:26.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生固态内核 最终\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you had a solid core that eventually drove
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.42,0:11:29.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地磁场像盾一样环绕着地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the protective magnetic field that surrounds our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.08,0:11:32.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果没有地磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Without the magnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.97,0:11:36.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球将没有空气 无法生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth would be an airless waste devoid of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.10,0:11:42.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳粒子风以每小时100英里的速度来到地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A gusty wind of materials speeds from the Sun past Earth at a million miles an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.28,0:11:45.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把大气不断的吹离 直到完全消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and could erode our atmosphere to nearly nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.43,0:11:47.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也只需几十万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a few million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.88,0:11:51.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是地磁场保护着地球抵御太阳风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Earth's magnetic field deflects the solar wind
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.27,0:11:53.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,保住了大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and preserves our air.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.20,0:11:59.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使有磁场保护\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But even with a magnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.10,0:12:02.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地表仍充满炎热和混乱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}violence and chaos continued to plague our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.15,0:12:05.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于炎热的铁核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Above the Earth's iron core,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.17,0:12:07.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,外层的岩石被融化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its rocky mantle was melting
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.73,0:12:10.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成突出地表的火山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}forming volcanoes that rose to the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.42,0:12:13.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不断释放有毒气体和火山灰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and burped up noxious gases and lava.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.87,0:12:19.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时小行星撞击依然不断发生着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the collisions kept coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.33,0:12:24.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球形成史上一次重要撞击改变了这一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One impact would forever change the course of Earth's history
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.70,0:12:27.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类的宿命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the fate of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.21,0:12:38.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球诞生5千万年后的某时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About 50 million years after the Earth began forming
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.31,0:12:42.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个巨大的撞击改变了地球发展方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it experienced a collision that would steer it in a new direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.92,0:12:46.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个火星大小的星体撞击地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An object the size of Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.08,0:12:51.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拥有当时地球体积80%大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}slammed right into Earth, which was already 80% of its total size.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.73,0:12:57.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大爆炸融化了两个星球的外表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The explosive impact melted both the planets' outer layers
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.86,0:13:01.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,融合并形成了一个更大的地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and fused the two together to form a larger Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.57,0:13:09.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些散落的其他碎片结合在一起形成了月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some molten debris that didn't blend together coalesced to shape our Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.77,0:13:20.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星体研究专家比尔首先发表了这样的理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Planetary scientist Bill Hartmann, first proposed this theory
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.36,0:13:23.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在美国国家航空航天局(NASA)的第一次登月任务之后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}after NASA's first mission to the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.49,0:13:28.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿波罗宇航员带回来一些岩石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Apollo astronauts brought back rocks from the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.00,0:13:33.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以了解这些岩石的产生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we could actually see what the rocks were made of,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.35,0:13:36.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后发现\Nthey found out that…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.29,0:13:40.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些岩石非常像地球上发现的火山岩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the rocks are like lava that you can find on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.87,0:13:45.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这表明地球和月球的构成非常相似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which tells you that the Moon material and the Earth material are very similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.27,0:13:51.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与地球关系密切的月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth's intimate relationship with its moon
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.76,0:13:54.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给地球成长带来诸多好处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gave the growing planet a competitive edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.12,0:13:58.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,月球的存在导致\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon is what causes the seasons because
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.97,0:14:02.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在一年的某些时候北极朝着太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some parts of the earthen North Pole is tilted toward the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.57,0:14:05.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一些时间 南极朝着太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and later on the South Pole is tilted toward the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.79,0:14:12.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,月球一直保持着一个倾角 在万有引力作用下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon holds that tilt steady. The various gravity forces that are exerted
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:16.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,始终保持在一个固定倾角\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tend to act in a way that holds that steady.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.28,0:14:22.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这次创造了月球的伟大的碰撞中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After the epic collision which created our moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.04,0:14:27.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球获得了超过90%的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our planet was over 90% of its total mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.68,0:14:32.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个地球形成过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The planetary formation process
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.90,0:14:35.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使地球具有生物进化的基础\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}involves almost a biological competition
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.21,0:14:39.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自于这些高速撞击获得的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of many bodies bashing into each other at very high speeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.10,0:14:48.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当39亿年前碰撞停止时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the collisions subsided nearly 3,9 billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.98,0:14:51.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系形成了8大行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our solar system was left with eight planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.38,0:14:54.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,包括冥王星则有9大行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or nine if you still count Pluto.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.38,0:14:58.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球处在了绕日运行的第三个位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth secured the third orbital position from the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.42,0:15:02.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离太阳930万英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is now 93 million miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.42,0:15:07.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几大行星各不相同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Planets don't like each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.72,0:15:09.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,取决于各自的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because they're gravitationally tugging each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.81,0:15:11.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,排列着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So they're equally spaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.23,0:15:16.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每个行星都一个一个隔着一定的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each planet is a certain fraction further from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.88,0:15:21.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些是太阳系中的流浪者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The objects that didn't become planets became refugees.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.58,0:15:24.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些小行星大多由石块和铁构成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Asteroids, made of rock and iron,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.08,0:15:28.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,存在于火星与木星的轨道之间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}found asylum in the Asteroid Belt between Mars and Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.48,0:15:32.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,彗星由冰 尘土和石块构成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Comets, composed of ices dust and rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.50,0:15:34.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些存在于太阳系的古比皮带\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sought shelter in the Kuiper Belt,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.89,0:15:36.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,位于海王星轨道外层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just beyond the planet Neptune.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.38,0:15:42.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一些聚集成奥尔特云远离地球10亿英里以外的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others migrated to the Oort Cloud, over a trillion miles from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.28,0:15:54.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常相似于这些撞坏的保时捷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This battered Porsches are a good analogue
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.18,0:15:56.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,包含着大量小行星和彗星的早期太阳系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the early Solar System, the comets and asteroids
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.95,0:15:59.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些小星体从诞生之初幸存下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that survived the early days.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.50,0:16:03.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同这些车一样保存着其所有部件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And like these cars, which are kept here for their parts,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.20,0:16:07.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们依然可以去寻找这些重要部件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can also ** comets and asteroids for vital parts
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.42,0:16:10.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些太阳系诞生之初就形成的小星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that have been stored since the formation of the Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.48,0:16:15.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球形成历史中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over the course of Earth's history,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.99,0:16:19.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些小行星可能改变了自己的运行轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}many misguided asteroids have strayed off their orbital path
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.29,0:16:23.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,落到地球上 成为地球的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and landed on our planet as meteorites.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.39,0:16:28.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,近年来 科学家们分析了这些外来物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over the years, scientists have analysed these meteorites
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.89,0:16:31.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过放射性同位素衰减测其年龄\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and determined their age through radioactive dating.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.31,0:16:35.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于它们与地球同时期诞生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And since meteorites were formed at the same time as our planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.12,0:16:38.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这也得出地球的年龄\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they provide the age of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.28,0:16:40.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大约45亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Roughly 4.5 billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.69,0:16:45.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家的这种特别思路\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientifically this is fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.42,0:16:48.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像寻找你的家族历史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's like looking at your family history
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.12,0:16:51.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想办法找出最初的家传物品\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and finding pieces of your first relative all the way
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.02,0:16:52.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,追溯他们的历史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}back in Earth's history.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.32,0:16:53.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然在外漂流很久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're still out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.92,0:16:58.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星和彗星们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Asteroids and comets
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.42,0:17:01.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时可能又是我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may also shed light
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.92,0:17:04.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上水的来源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the origins of water on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.22,0:17:13.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,39亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}3.9 billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.22,0:17:18.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球开始冷却 形成坚硬的硅酸盐外壳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Earth cooled, forming a thick silicate crust over its mantle,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.22,0:17:20.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,覆盖在铁镍内核之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an iron and nickel core.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.22,0:17:26.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很快地温暖的地面覆盖了大量的水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Warm liquid soon covered the planet's surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.92,0:17:29.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除了点缀在地球上的一些火山岛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}except for a few volcanic islands dotting the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.32,0:17:35.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的又一个特别幸运之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the Earth's lucky properties
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.82,0:17:38.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是诞生在一个恰当的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that it happened to be born in just the right place,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.32,0:17:40.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一个适合生存的区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in what's called the habitable zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.89,0:17:42.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跟太阳保持足够的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the right distance from the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.32,0:17:44.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋不会被蒸发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where its ocean does not boil away,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.49,0:17:46.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为不是太热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but not too hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.22,0:17:48.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同样又离太阳不是太远海洋也不至于被冰冻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or too far away, where its ocean freezes over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.82,0:17:57.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是地表的这么多水来自何方？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But where did Earth get all this water?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.02,0:18:03.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种假说认为是来自于火山爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One view is that water came from volcanoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.52,0:18:07.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些早期地球上所存在的大量火山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which have been around since the early formation of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.42,0:18:14.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向大气中喷发了大量水蒸气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Volcanoes spewed out massive amounts of steam into the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.62,0:18:20.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球降温的过程中结成雨水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Earth cooled, volcanic steam condensed into rain
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.52,0:18:23.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是向地面注入了大量的水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and thereby supplied the planet with water.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.19,0:18:31.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是火山的水源来自何方？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But where did the steamy water emitted from volcanoes come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.18,0:18:38.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火山运动循环着许多物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Volcanoes basically recycle material from melted rock
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.40,0:18:40.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地表的任何覆盖物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the mantle of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.70,0:18:42.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,包括水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Including water.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.70,0:18:46.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然这不是凭空创造的水来自于早期海洋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But that's not really new water in the sense that it was there before in the oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.90,0:18:50.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经循环了许多次了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and is coming out again for a second time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.80,0:18:58.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美国国家航空航天局(NASA) 科学家 迈克尔·穆马\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASA's senior scientist, Michael Mumma,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.59,0:19:01.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,认为地球上的水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}says our planet's water
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.50,0:19:03.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}came from space.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.00,0:19:09.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些由冰组成的彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Comets, which are made up of frozen gases,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.50,0:19:11.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给地球来了一场淋浴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could have showered Earth with water
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.78,0:19:15.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球形成之初就不断发生着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}during the relentless impacts of its infancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.20,0:19:19.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些小冰体提供的水量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The deliver of water from an icy body
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.10,0:19:23.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,取决于他们的大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}depends very critically on how large the particle is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.60,0:19:27.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,较小的个体在大气层外部就蒸发了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The smaller bodies that came in would break up high in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.50,0:19:31.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其他的才能把他们的物质留在地表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The other bodies delivered their material to the surface of the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.40,0:19:34.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们自身蒸发后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they can actually vaporize that material
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.10,0:19:36.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成为地球上的水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that becomes the water on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.60,0:19:44.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,穆马试图证实水是否是来自彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mumma is trying to determine if cometary water
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.78,0:19:47.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,彗星的水组成成分应该跟地球一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is made up of the same ingredients as our planet's water.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.40,0:19:55.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道海洋中拥有地球上水的混合物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know the Earth's oceans contain a mixture of normal water,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.20,0:19:57.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水(氧化氢)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}H2O,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.20,0:20:00.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与重水(氧化氘)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and heavy water, HDO,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.70,0:20:02.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,含有氘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which includes deuterium,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.60,0:20:06.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种氢的同位素 为氢质量的两倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a form of hydrogen that is twice as heavy as normal hydrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.70,0:20:12.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是研究彗星十分困难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But comets are difficult to study.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.10,0:20:14.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们极少靠近地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Few pass near our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.00,0:20:18.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绝大部分都在太阳系外部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because most orbit in the outer solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.12,0:20:26.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过在1986年 欧洲空间局发射的探测器乔托号近距离地访问了一个彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in 1986, Europe's Giotto spacecraft had a close encounter with Comet Halley,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.30,0:20:29.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,著名的哈雷彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}also known as Halley's Comet,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.80,0:20:32.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,距离地球3800万英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which was 38 million miles from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.40,0:20:36.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个分析样本的方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the ways we analyze samples
