Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.30,0:20:46.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用这种方法精确地测量气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we can measure the gases very accurately in this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:48.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自于哈雷彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was done for Comet Halley.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.70,0:20:55.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哈雷彗星的水相似于地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Comet Halley's water is similar to that on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.60,0:20:59.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是目前分析的其他彗星的水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, the other comets analyzed so far,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.90,0:21:04.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,重水比例是地球水的两倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have twice the amount of HDO, or heavy water, that's in our oceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.33,0:21:09.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们也开始观察彗星的其他化合物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know now, by looking at other compounds in comets,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.84,0:21:11.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并不都相同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that they're not all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.34,0:21:14.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此我们不知道哈雷彗星是否\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we don't know whether Comet Halley
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.95,0:21:18.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是最有代表的彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was in fact representative of all comets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.97,0:21:22.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们目前研究的彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most comets studied thus far
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.37,0:21:26.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多处于古比皮带位于太阳系外部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have come from the Kuiper Belt, located in the outer solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.22,0:21:31.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些彗星也许跟地球形成没有联系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, they probably didn't help form planet Earth.
