Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.76,0:26:53.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的几乎每个角落\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every niche on this planet for energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.22,0:26:58.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有人称这些低等生物为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some have dubbed these early life forms
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.70,0:27:01.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗜温生物或嗜极生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}extremophiles or thermophiles,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.72,0:27:05.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是能在极端环境下生存的微生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}organisms that can live in extreme environments.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.24,0:27:09.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象一下有大量流行撞击地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let's say there was a massive meteorite that hit the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.66,0:27:13.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温度升到40多度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the temperature of the Earth went up 40 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.89,0:27:17.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很好 很适合这些嗜温生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, that would be just perfect for these extremophiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.67,0:27:21.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如我们所知 像这些生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the things we know, for instance, is that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.82,0:27:26.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常相似于远古的那些生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the"oldest" organisms, the ones that are nearest to the last common ancestor,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.44,0:27:28.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都是这样的嗜温生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are all thermophilic organisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.26,0:27:32.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可能要问 生命如何在如此的高温下进化？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you could say, well that proves that life evolved at high temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.46,0:27:41.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今这些生物的后代 能适应更高的温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Descendents of these hot-blooded organisms can be found today
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.52,0:27:46.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够生存在华氏230度的高温中\Nand they can live at temperatures of 230 ℃.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.64,0:27:52.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想见识这些所谓嗜温生物 来黄石国家公园\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you want some so called thermophiles, then you go to Yellowstone
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.08,0:27:56.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会发现这些沸腾的湖 像煮沸的开水锅\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you see these bubbling lakes and cauldrons of smelly water.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.26,0:28:00.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,亿万年来 这里看起来依然是不毛之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And for years people assumed they were sterile,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.39,0:28:02.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其实却充满着生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but they're full of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.11,0:28:06.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有适合生存于此的生命体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And only these organisms* adapting to that extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.07,0:28:11.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些现代嗜温生物表明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Modern day extremophiles may prove
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.74,0:28:14.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生命的能够生存和适应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that life could have survived and adapted
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.41,0:28:18.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如地球早期的那些极端环境之下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}under the extreme conditions on Earth during its turbulent infancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.16,0:28:24.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是这些单细胞生物如何进化成复杂高等生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But, how could single-celled microbes transform into complex life?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.60,0:28:32.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大约在30亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Approximately 3 billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.04,0:28:37.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,原始生物靠吸收太阳能生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}primitive life soaked up energy from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.09,0:28:45.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些水中微生物具有叶绿素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Underwater microbes formed a green pigment called chlorophyll.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.59,0:28:48.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够吸收太阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This enabled them to trap sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.62,0:28:50.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并通过一些化学反应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and produce a chemical reaction
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.77,0:28:54.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把二氧化碳和水变成养料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which converts carbon dioxide and water into food.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.08,0:29:03.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个过程--光合作用过程使得这些细菌聚集起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This process, called photosynthesis, led the way for bacteria to multiply
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.18,0:29:05.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成地球上的最初的多细胞结构 藻青菌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into one of Earth's earlier structures: cyanobacteria,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.10,0:29:08.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是所知的"蓝藻"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}formerly called"blue-green algae".
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.68,0:29:13.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蓝藻开始从水中大量释放氧气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cyanobacteria injected vast amounts of free oxygen into the water and air
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.55,0:29:17.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆发了一场氧气革命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and sparked the oxygen revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.74,0:29:24.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不久生命开始分两个方向进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All of a sudden, life divided into two groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.45,0:29:29.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一部分是无需氧气的厌氧生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One that ran away from the oxygen and hid in the anaerobic part of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.60,0:29:32.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其他的则使用氧气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the other that started using the oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.43,0:29:35.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用来燃烧消耗能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a great energetic advantage,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.67,0:29:38.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后它们能够进化的更大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then could evolve, I think, to be much bigger,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.09,0:29:41.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以及进化的更快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and perhaps to evolve much faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.16,0:29:47.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相信这些蓝藻需要更大的身体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One thing is for sure, when the cyanobacteria got this ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.20,0:29:49.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与其他个体竞争\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they outcompeted everybody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.50,0:30:00.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,得益于这些菌类 生命快速地多样化起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thanks to cyanobacteria, life was able to quickly diversify
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.88,0:30:02.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,变得越来越复杂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and become more complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.47,0:30:08.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有他们就没有氧分子的大量存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Without it, molecular oxygen wouldn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.76,0:30:14.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也将不会进化出任何动植物和人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Therefore, plants, animals and humans would have never developed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.95,0:30:23.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有它们 怎能有今天的我们？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if we didn't have the cyanobacteria we wouldn't be around.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.13,0:30:27.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们是这些地球微生物的后代\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We owe our heritage to the scum of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.68,0:30:33.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都从同一个地方进化而来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All of us came from the same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.31,0:30:39.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们都有许多共同点 跟这些微生物一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have so many things in common with bacteria
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.34,0:30:42.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些是毋庸置疑的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that there's just no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.61,0:30:51.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,莫哈韦沙漠死亡之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Mojave Desert, near Death Valley
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.89,0:30:55.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,位于南加利福尼亚看起来没有生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in Southern California, appears void of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.17,0:31:03.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但在这些干涸的湖床之下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But below the surface of this dry lake bed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.68,0:31:07.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类的最初远祖繁衍着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}mankind's ancestors thrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.49,0:31:18.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上那些最初的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Planet Earth's earliest life forms
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.34,0:31:23.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够适应如此极端的环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may have adapted and persevered under extreme conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.18,0:31:37.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今 在干旱荒芜的南加州莫哈韦沙漠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Today, in the parched and barren Mojave Desert, in Southern California,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.82,0:31:42.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地理生物学家肯恩·尼尔森整探寻着生命的秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}geobiologist Ken Nealson is searching for the secrets to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.17,0:31:47.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发现现代微生物们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He's discovered that modern microbial organisms
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.47,0:31:51.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,依然繁衍在这样的不毛之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}also thrive in some inhospitable places.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.46,0:31:56.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,观察这里你能发现什么？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What you see when you glance at this environment are
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.77,0:32:00.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看起来是很多这样的沟壑与土堆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a bunch of what appear to be tunnels or mounds here,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.61,0:32:04.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,却是由生活着的微生物排出的大量气体所造成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and these are made by the gases produced by the microbes living
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.29,0:32:06.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而这原本是平整的土地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in this mudflat area.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.24,0:32:11.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你带了水 并淋湿这块土壤\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we were to take water and rehydrate this piece of dirt
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.54,0:32:13.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把它放到显微镜之下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and put this under the microscope,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.25,0:32:16.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会发现水里飘满了微生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would be rife with abundant microbes swimming everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.99,0:32:20.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是繁衍在这些贫瘠土地之中的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this is the lifecycle on the saltflat,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.36,0:32:22.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们所称的这些嗜极生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all of which we call extremophiles,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.99,0:32:26.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很好的生存于这样的荒原上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and which eke out an existence in a mudflat like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.69,0:32:34.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,微生物统治着整个地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Microbes reigned supreme for much of Earth's history.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.90,0:32:36.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,改变着整个世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They revolutionized the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.82,0:32:41.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为高等物种的出现创造了条件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and paved the way for a myriad of sophisticated species.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.73,0:32:46.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过直到陆地的大块出现才给了生物们一个新家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it was land that gave life a new home.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.07,0:32:51.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也就是陆地上升时期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's believed the emergence of landmass began roughly
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.27,0:32:54.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大约始于40亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}4 billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.00,0:32:58.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地壳板块运动的不断加热和挤压\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Plate tectonics created heat and pressure,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.70,0:33:02.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从海平面上升起大量岩石 陆地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that produced rock lighter than the ocean floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.38,0:33:04.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随后不断的飘浮与结合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It ultimately floated and accumulated
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.95,0:33:09.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成了大块的陆地 并不断地改变的形状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creating continents that would change in size and shape over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.02,0:33:14.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球大陆的出现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The presence of vast continents would enable Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.69,0:33:17.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,承载着这独特的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to sustain its most distinctive component,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.38,0:33:20.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,复杂高等生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}complex life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.56,0:33:29.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经过超过20亿年的不断进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After 2 billion years of planetary and biological evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.85,0:33:34.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最初的两栖射生物开始爬上陆地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the first plants and animals emerged from water onto land.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.27,0:33:39.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是数亿年后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it would take hundreds of millions of years
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.05,0:33:43.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类出现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before humans evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.40,0:33:48.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自从人类统治这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And once Man claimed dominance over the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.05,0:33:51.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球永远将是独一无二的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth would never be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.77,0:33:58.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球是人类最佳栖息处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Planet Earth now holds the best real estate
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.11,0:34:00.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太阳系中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for mankind in our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.96,0:34:04.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,7大洲和无数岛屿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Seven diverse continents and countless islands
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.91,0:34:07.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是60亿人口的家园\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are home to 6 billion people.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.46,0:34:17.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常难以置信地生存于地球上多数时期的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yet, remarkably, most of Earth's existence thus far,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.00,0:34:20.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并不是人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been without humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.26,0:34:29.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将整个地球历史比作一个24小时的钟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The planet's history has been compared to a 24-hour clock,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.90,0:34:34.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类的出现只是1天的最后2秒钟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the presence of Man being the last 2 seconds of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.92,0:34:51.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们现在围绕跑到缓慢驾驶\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're driving around the track now at a relatively modest speed
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.42,0:34:55.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样行驶平稳易于掌控\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in this car that handles very smoothly. A very controlled ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.21,0:34:59.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对我来说就像地球上的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This reminds me of life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.27,0:35:02.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,盛衰变换着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Life on Earth has had its ups and downs,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.23,0:35:04.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相比较于其他行星的发展\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but compared to evolution of other planets
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.82,0:35:09.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数亿年时间里都非常相似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Earth has had a relatively smooth ride for billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.33,0:35:12.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是生命繁衍于此的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's why life has flourished here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.08,0:35:23.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在随着人类对未来的改变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But with mankind now navigating its future,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.65,0:35:28.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球这艘太空船开始发生剧烈变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Spaceship Earth may return to its tumultuous beginnings.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.16,0:35:33.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类使用各种手段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Humans, through trial-and-error evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.47,0:35:37.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使得地球适合人类居住 成为一个特别的星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are suited to live on this particular planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.38,0:35:41.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像现在这样 而不管将来如何\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, that's true right now. We don't know if that will be true in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.52,0:35:47.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同样地 人类创造了大量难以置信的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earthlings created what once would seem almost unimaginable.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.34,0:35:50.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科技\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.11,0:35:54.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,车辆 机械和电子仪器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mechanical vehicles, gadgets and gizmos
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.20,0:35:56.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,简化并改进着我们的生活\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have simplified and bettered our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.68,0:36:03.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大多数制品所依赖的于化学材料 燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many of these conveniences are run on or made using fossil fuels,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.62,0:36:06.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都是从地壳中获得\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which are harvested from the Earth's crust.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.73,0:36:13.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是最近100年来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But over the last hundred years,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.07,0:36:17.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的改变引起了一些全球化的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our innovations have gotten us into planetary trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.07,0:36:23.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类对地球的影响越来越大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Humans are having a major effect on Planet Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.36,0:36:26.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像全球变暖和人口爆炸问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with global warming, and population explosion,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.57,0:36:30.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给环境造成巨大影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so we're having a very large effect on the environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.02,0:36:33.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温室效应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The natural greenhouse effect
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.78,0:36:36.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是指大气吸收红外辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the absorption of infrared radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.17,0:36:38.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,保持地球温暖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by our atmosphere, which warms our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.56,0:36:45.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有温室气体地球表面会比现在低86华氏度\NWithout greenhouse gases, the Earth's surface would be up to 86 ℉ cooler.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.27,0:36:50.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是最近20年温室气体增长过快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in the last 20 years there's been an increase in greenhouse gases,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.28,0:36:52.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,特别是二氧化碳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}especially carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.13,0:36:54.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生于化学燃料燃烧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}produced by burning fossil fuels.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.74,0:36:58.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温度的上升直接影响到农业\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The increased heating is affecting agriculture,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.52,0:37:01.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海平面和气候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sea level and weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.50,0:37:05.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,过去二氧化碳含量也曾提升\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the past, carbon dioxide levels had spiked
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.68,0:37:09.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是自然火山生成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}due to natural causes, such as volcanic outgassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.18,0:37:15.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而增长比想象的要快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, today's rises seem to be happening much more rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.29,0:37:23.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了观察温室效应带来的巨大的变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To visibly witness the drastic changes
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.86,0:37:29.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们来到不适宜人类居住的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one needs to travel to the barely habitable zones on Planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.21,0:37:33.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个长的像人类的冰山将\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There, mankind's future
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.21,0:37:36.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,逐渐融化消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is literally melting away.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.36,0:37:53.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的南北极众所周知的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth's North and South Poles are known as the cryospheres,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.47,0:37:57.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拥有大量冰雪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}regions blanketed with snow and ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.92,0:38:03.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,调节着地球气温与水平面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They help regulate climate temperature and water levels around the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.97,0:38:09.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美国国家航空航天局(NASA)科学家-瓦里得·阿布德拉底\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASA Senior Scientist, Waleed Abdalati,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.98,0:38:12.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,调查世界上的冰冻区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}investigates the frozen parts of our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.05,0:38:18.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,站在冰上感觉很奇妙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The feeling of being on the ice is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.45,0:38:25.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常荣幸的能够踏上这些地方 这就是我第一次站在冰面上的感受\NIt's pristine…in places where probably my boots have been to touch the ground there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.07,0:38:27.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会觉得自己很渺小\NIt's very humbling…
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.74,0:38:34.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,站在那儿你感受到一种巨大 非常难忘\NYou stand there and it's so vast and impressive…
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.91,0:38:38.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是最近一个世纪以来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in the last century,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.23,0:38:41.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们比如阿布德拉底博士\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists like Dr. Abdalati
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.79,0:38:45.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,证实了冰层的消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have personally witnessed Earth's ice shrinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.37,0:38:51.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,原因是白色的冰雪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The reason: ice and snow are white,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.57,0:38:54.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,反射阳光冷却地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they reflect sunlight and cool the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.10,0:38:58.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相反的海洋吸收阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By contrast, the open oceans absorb sunlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.44,0:38:59.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温暖地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which heats the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.85,0:39:04.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而融化的冰产生了更多水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, as ice melts, it creates more open water
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.74,0:39:08.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吸收了更多阳光使地球更温暖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which sucks in more sunlight and increasingly warms the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.56,0:39:10.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后又融化更多的冰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and melts more ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.90,0:39:14.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们说这是不稳定状态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's unstable, we say,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.82,0:39:17.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使一个小的改变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because even the slightest change
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.68,0:39:19.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也会带来巨大变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tends to amplify itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.06,0:39:23.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很典型的恶性循环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's essentially a runaway effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.90,0:39:29.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地极现在很危险\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth's polar ice caps are in peril.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.37,0:39:33.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些持续融化的宝贵风景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Continually melting of these precious landscapes
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.54,0:39:37.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许会在某个时刻带来灾难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may one day produce catastrophes across the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.52,0:39:48.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在南极\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the South Pole, the continent of Antarctica,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.05,0:39:50.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那儿拥有世界70%的淡水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}holds 70% of the world's fresh water.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.07,0:39:55.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些大陆边缘的冰保护着内部的冰 就像胡佛大坝那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ice shelves surrounding the continent hold back ice like the Hoover Dam.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.73,0:39:57.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是现在很脆弱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But they are weakening.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.31,0:40:01.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经存在了超过12000年的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After 12.000 years of solidity
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.84,0:40:05.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拉森 B冰层仅仅在5周时间就坍塌消失了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Larsen B Ice Shelf collapsed in just 5 weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.69,0:40:11.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在北极\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the North Pole,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.94,0:40:15.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有人预言 北冰洋夏天将不再结冰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some predict that the Arctic Ocean will be ice-free during the summer
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.68,0:40:17.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许仅仅只是40-60年之后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the next 40 to 60 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.59,0:40:22.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样的高温到底是如果产生的？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's causing the warm temperatures
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.43,0:40:25.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一部分是自然 自身的变化原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}certainly there's an element of natural variability,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.60,0:40:28.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是人的作用更不可忽视\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but there is also a human contribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.88,0:40:32.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道人类促使全球气温上升\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know that humans are contributing to the warmer environment
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.28,0:40:36.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这加速了冰层的消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that we're subsequently contributing to diminish ice cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.48,0:40:42.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在格陵兰岛雅各布港冰川\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In Greenland, the Jakobshavn Glacier,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.50,0:40:45.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,世界上流动最快的冰川\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one of the fastest flowing glaciers in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.57,0:40:48.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像运行着的一列火车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is now moving like a runaway train.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.70,0:40:51.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在它快速运动着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it's now going about
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.18,0:40:55.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每小时5英尺\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}5 ft/hour, which believe me, for a glacier is very fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.80,0:41:00.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最糟糕的情况就是所有冰川\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The worst-case scenario would be that all of these glaciers
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.57,0:41:05.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,越来越来地流失 大量的冰流入海中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}start to speed up and just deliver huge amounts of ice to the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.87,0:41:09.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这将提升海平面差不多3英尺\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That would be a 3-foot increase worldwide.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.13,0:41:12.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在海岸临近区域 3英尺意味着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And 3 feet in coastal regions
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.88,0:41:16.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冲击至少千万计的人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is plenty to displace millions and millions of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.48,0:41:28.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然人类可以迁移到稳定地区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although humans may be able to stabilize
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.84,0:41:32.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是人类制造的垃圾 最多几十年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}man-made pollutants, it might take decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.84,0:41:36.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这时自然界的破坏就将起作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the same time, there are natural processes at work
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.17,0:41:39.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,决定人类的命运\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that might determine mankind's fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.75,0:41:43.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球会一直进行自身的发展进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The planet's going through its own evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.25,0:41:47.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们对地球的所做只会影响我们自己 而非地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we do to the planet affects us, it doesn't affect the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.88,0:41:50.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以建一个大气的模型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we may mock up with the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.11,0:41:53.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上千年的全球变暖之类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a few thousand years of global warming and so forth,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.37,0:41:57.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上这只对人类而言很重要\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but this is actually just a blip. It's an important blip to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.49,0:42:00.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于行星自身发展不重要\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's not necessarily a blip in terms of planetary evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.26,0:42:08.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,唐纳德·布朗利 和 彼得·沃德\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Donald Brownlee and colleague Peter Ward
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.96,0:42:11.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,测量了一些地球上生命赖以生存的信号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have measured our planet's vital signs,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.76,0:42:14.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,预计结果令人担忧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its prognosis it's bleak.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.37,0:42:18.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球作为动物和人类的生存之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth, as a place for animal and human life,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.29,0:42:20.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始进入老年时期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is nearing old age.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.56,0:42:22.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.84,0:42:27.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳将越来越亮 越热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Sun is getting brighter and hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.98,0:42:31.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上高等生物面临的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The problem down the line for advanced life on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.36,0:42:35.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是因为太阳变得更亮了些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that as the Sun gets slightly brighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.39,0:42:36.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,假设\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the expectation is
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.96,0:42:41.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完全去除大气中的全部二氧化碳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that carbon dioxide will be almost completely removed from the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.74,0:42:45.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这会导致地球动植物的灭亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There will be an end to the age of plants and animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.42,0:42:58.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类也将在500万年内灭亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Humans could die out 500 million years from now
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.54,0:43:00.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为越来越热的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}due to the brightening of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.88,0:43:04.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是 在一些完美计划下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in the grand scheme of things
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.59,0:43:07.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类或许能顺利发展\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Man may have had a good run.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.16,0:43:10.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,躲过灭亡的命运\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before reaching extinction,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.73,0:43:14.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类将可以生存在更复杂的环境下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perhaps humans will have lived longer than any other complex species
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.02,0:43:19.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过自身努力改变自然环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because of their ability to adapt to changing environmental conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.51,0:43:23.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从人类视角来看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From a human standpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.30,0:43:27.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,保时捷中的地球司机像其它行星将继续行驶\Nthe Earth will remain been a Porsche planet probably for another…
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.74,0:43:30.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,5或10亿年时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}half a billion to a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.35,0:43:34.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个时间单位\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which is a truly awesome timescale
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.44,0:43:36.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于人类实在太长了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from a human standpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.26,0:43:47.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过利用地球上来历不明的水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As Spaceship Earth manoeuvres through uncharted waters,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.45,0:43:52.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类思考着地球诞生的奇异之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}humankind can reflect on the planet's awesome achievements
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.63,0:43:54.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球自身又坚毅地生存于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and steadfast survival
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.30,0:43:57.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,荒凉的邻空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the tough neighbourhood
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.60,0:43:59.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called THE UNIVERSE.
